DLQ = Dead Letter Queue — a separate queue that stores failed messages.

SNS DLQ stores messages that SNS failed to deliver to the subscriber — delivery problem. SQS DLQ stores messages that the consumer received but failed to process after max retries — processing problem.

Key point:

+---------------------+-------------------+------------------------------+
|                     | SNS DLQ           | SQS DLQ                      |
+---------------------+-------------------+------------------------------+
| Stores full message | ✗ No              | ✓ Yes                        |
| Can reprocess       | ✗ No              | ✓ Yes                        |
| Stores error info   | ✓ Yes             | ✓ Yes                        |
| Purpose             | Debug delivery    | Reprocess failed messages    |
|                     | failure           |                              |
+---------------------+-------------------+------------------------------+
